ce for more than twenty years. Few musicians of any era have had a broader experience, wider sphere of influence, and greater number of significant and varied accomplishments.Preceded by a comprehensive Preface, these "Autobiographical Recollections," narrated in the last months of Widor's life, are translated into English for the first time, meticulously edited, and profusely annotated. The persons, political details, and historical events that Widor spoke of with great fluency are identified in notes that give the reader a full understanding of the narrative. Several appendixes and a trove of hitherto unpublished photos illuminate the text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aComposerszFrancevBiography. 0aOrganistszFrancevBiography. 4aBiography & Memoirs. 4aModern History. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Individual Composer & Musician.2bisacsh  aAcademy of Fine Arts.  aCavaillé-Coll.  aOrgan Toccata.  aOrgan symphonies.  aOrganist.  aRomantic era.  aRomantics.  aSaint-Sulpice.1 aNear, John R, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Rollin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805432920?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805432920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805432920/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles